			<ns0:name>noelal...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/113000403807150741221/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The windows implementation of locks does not check if CreateMutex fails, and instead sets the member unconditionally.   With an invalid mutex, attempts to lock will return immediately with error.   Neither Try nor Lock check for this case, so Try will always fail possibly causing a deadlock, while Lock will always return immediately causing incorrect behavior.

This poses a both a correctness and security issue where exhaustion of OS mutex resources could cause the TCB to behave incorrectly.
